"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127300","Department for Education","false","2019-05-23","<p>The Department has not undertaken such an estimate.</p><p>As part of the Government’s 2014 review of survivor benefits in occupational pension schemes, in assessing the likely cost of retrospectively equalising survivor benefits for past periods of accrual, the Government Actuary’s Department did estimate what proportion of female members of the scheme have service before 1988. Further information can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/occupational-pension-schemes-review-of-survivor-benefits" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/occupational-pension-schemes-review-of-survivor-benefits</a>.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2019-05-23T14:18:27.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127300/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127300/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127300/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-05-17","Teachers: Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate he has made of the number of women who made superannuation contributions to the Teachers Pension Scheme prior to 6 April 1988.","false","Biography information for Janet Daby","Lewisham East","Janet Daby","255699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127301","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-05-23","<p>The number of domestic solar installations during April 2019 will be published by BEIS on Thursday 30 May using information from the MCS (Microgeneration Certification Scheme) installation database. These are provisional numbers which are subject to revision in future publications.</p><p> </p><p>Solar photovoltaic deployment statistics is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/solar-photovoltaics-deployment" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/solar-photovoltaics-deployment</a>.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2019-05-23T13:53:11.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127301/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127301/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127301/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-05-17","Solar Power: Feed-in Tariffs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what estimate he has made of the volume of rooftop solar that has been deployed since the closure of the  Feed-In Tariff scheme and the Export Tariff.","false","Biography information for Wera Hobhouse","Bath","Wera Hobhouse","255693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127302","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-05-23","<p>HM Courts and Tribunal’s Service supports the provision of its Welsh Language Scheme as applicable in both Wales and England. HMCTS service centres that provide a national service welcome correspondence in Welsh, which will be dealt with within the same time frame and to the same standards as English language correspondence.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2019-05-23T13:26:55.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127302/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127302/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127302/answer","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127302/answer/previousversion/119640","Biography information for Paul Maynard","54","Justice","Justice","2019-05-17","HM Courts and Tribunals Service: Welsh Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether Welsh language speakers are able to correspond with Her Majesty's Courts and Tribunals Service in England through the medium of the Welsh language.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","255658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127303","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-05-23","<p>A Royal Military Police Company, Cadet detachment, and associated Cadet headquarters are based at the site. Currently, 77 cadets attend eight hours of training there each week. An additional 388 cadets have passed through the facility between 5 December 2006 and 24 January 2019.</p><p>When there is spare capacity, the site is used for training by other Government Departments and for wider defence purposes.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","255675","2019-05-23T14:39:59.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127303/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127303/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1127303/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-05-17","Royal Military Police: Lambeth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many hours the Ministry of Defence Royal Military Police Centre on Upper Tulse Hill SW2 2RS is used per week.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Chuka Umunna","255674"
